  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Enrichment Center Manager (Tampines)",
  "description": "<p><strong>1. Centre Operations & Administration</strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee daily centre operations, opening and closing procedures</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with MOE, ECDA (if applicable), and company policies</p></li><li><p>Manage class schedules, room usage, and centre resources</p></li><li><p>Handle student enrolment, withdrawals, transfers, and records</p></li><li><p>Ensure cleanliness, safety, and readiness of the centre at all times</p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Academic & Teaching Quality</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support and supervise teachers to ensure lesson quality and consistency</p></li><li><p>Monitor curriculum delivery and student learning outcomes</p></li><li><p>Conduct class observations and provide constructive feedback</p></li><li><p>Coordinate assessments, progress reports, and parent feedback</p></li><li><p>Uphold CMA’s teaching standards and academic values</p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Staff Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Recruit, onboard, train, and retain teaching and admin staff</p></li><li><p>Prepare staff schedules, leave planning, and duty rosters</p></li><li><p>Conduct performance reviews and coaching sessions</p></li><li><p>Foster a positive, professional, and collaborative centre culture</p></li></ul><p><strong>4. Customer Experience & Parent Engagement</strong></p><ul><li><p>Serve as the main point of contact for parents and guardians</p></li><li><p>Handle enquiries, feedback, and complaints professionally</p></li><li><p>Conduct parent meetings, consultations, and open houses</p></li><li><p>Build long-term trust and relationships with families</p></li></ul><p><strong>5. Sales, Marketing & Growth</strong></p><ul><li><p>Drive student enrolment and retention targets</p></li><li><p>Execute centre-level marketing initiatives and promotions</p></li><li><p>Support trial classes, school partnerships, and community outreach</p></li><li><p>Track and report enrolment numbers, conversion rates, and revenue</p></li></ul>",
